description: Retrieves GuardDuty member accounts (of the current GuardDuty administrator account) specified by the account IDs.

parameters.name: DetectorId
parameters.description: The unique ID of the detector of the GuardDuty account whose members you want to retrieve. To find the detectorId in the current Region, see the Settings page in the GuardDuty console, or run the ListDetectors API.

parameters.name: AccountIds
parameters.description: A list of account IDs of the GuardDuty member accounts that you want to describe. (string) ---

nested_items.name: AccountId
nested_items.description: The ID of the member account.

nested_items.name: DetectorId
nested_items.description: The detector ID of the member account.

nested_items.name: Email
nested_items.description: The email address of the member account.

nested_items.name: RelationshipStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the relationship between the member and the administrator.

nested_items.name: InvitedAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp when the invitation was sent.

nested_items.name: UpdatedAt
nested_items.description: The last-updated timestamp of the member.

nested_items.name: UnprocessedAccounts
nested_items.description: A list of objects that contain the unprocessed account and a result string that explains why it was unprocessed.

nested_items.name: AccountId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services account ID.

nested_items.name: Result
nested_items.description: A reason why the account hasn't been processed.
